      <h1 class='title'>Tri-Service and Army Training</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 18 December 2002 vol 396 c57WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_57ws' title='Col. 57WS &mdash; HC Deb 18 December 2002 vol 396 c57WS' name='column_57ws' href='#column_57ws' rel='bookmark'>57WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0396P0_20021218_CWS_19'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-adam-ingram' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0396P0_20021218_CWS_19' title='Link to this speech by Mr Adam Ingram' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-adam-ingram" title="Mr Adam Ingram">The Minister of State, Ministry of Defence (Mr. Adam Ingram)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">On 17 October (<span class="italic">Official Report,</span> column 571) I announced that a special appraisal of the initial training of non-Officer recruits of all three services would take place. This review was to be conducted independent of Service and commands and to report directly to Ministers. The work is nearing completion and I now plan to make findings public in January next year.</p><p>Surrey Police continue their investigation into deaths at Deepcut and it would be inappropriate to comment on this area until their inquiry is complete.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
